    "narrative": "The **Zurich Zebras** enter today\u2019s slate with a high-ceiling core, anchored by **Christian Yelich** (72.61) and **Trea Turner** (71.43). **Christian Yelich** draws a prime matchup against Littell, where a significant platoon advantage (+13%) and a favorable hitting environment elevate him to our top start. Meanwhile, **Trea Turner** remains an essential cornerstone; despite facing a formidable arm in Gallen, his leadoff spot (+10% order bonus) and elite sprint speed floor make him a lock. We are also capitalizing on high-upside opportunities with **Caleb Durbin** (67.85) and **Kyle Schwarber** (67.82). **Caleb Durbin** benefits from a rare alignment of favorable wind and a weak matchup against Pallante, while **Kyle Schwarber** continues to provide high-leverage power output despite the tough draw against Gallen.\n\nThe primary bench dilemma today involved **Victor Scott II** (58.31), who pushed for a spot due to his elite speed profile but ultimately missed the cut. While **Victor Scott II** offers superior SB potential, he was penalized by a ninth-order projection (-8%), making the efficiency of **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (61.24) or the platoon-heavy upside of **Josh Smith** (62.54) more attractive in the aggregate. Caution is advised regarding **Yordan Alvarez** (55.60); while he remains a must-start talent, his score is suppressed today by an elite matchup against Gilbert. We are essentially betting on talent over context there, accepting a lower efficiency floor to avoid benching our biggest slugger. As we monitor wind trends, keep an eye on **Dillon Dingler** (48.11), who remains a marginal start; if the environment shifts, we have the flexibility to adjust, but for now, the lineup is optimized to maximize both Roto category depth and daily efficiency.",
